-- Alstom Agrees to Build $40 Million Geothermal Project in Mexico
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-11-12T16:50:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-12/alstom-agrees-to-build-40-million-geothermal-project-in-mexico.html
Alstom SA (ALO) , the French maker of power
equipment, was awarded a 30 million-euro ($40.3 million)
contract to build a geothermal plant for Mexico’s state-run
utility Comision Federal de Electricidad.  The Los Humeros III – Phase A power project in the eastern
municipality of Chignautla will have 25 megawatts of capacity,
Paris-based Alstom said today in a  statement . It’s expected to
begin operations in the second quarter of 2016.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
